        "startScan": 1778712396221,
        "URL": "data:text/html;charset=utf-8,%3C!doctype%20html%3E%0A%3Chtml%20lang%3D%22%22%3E%0A%3Chead%3E%0A%20%20%3Cmeta%20charset%3D%22utf-8%22%3E%0A%20%20%3Ctitle%3EReturn%20Point%20Memory%3C%2Ftitle%3E%0A%3C%2Fhead%3E%0A%3Cbody%3E%0A%3Cbody%3E%0A%0A%3Ch1%3EReturn%20Point%20Memory%2C%20or%20Wiping%20Out%20(Dahmen%2C%20Perkovic'%3B%0A%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fpub.html%2366%22%3E66%2C%2068%2C%2069%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fpub.html%2375%22%3E%2075%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fh1%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%0AHysteresis%20is%20the%20history%20dependence%20of%20a%20material%20under%20an%20external%0Astrain.%20%20If%20one%20bends%20a%20table%20fork%20too%20far%2C%20it%20won't%20spring%20back%20to%0Aits%20original%20shape%3A%20past%20the%20elastic%20limit%2C%20the%20fork%20exhibits%20hysteresis.%0AUnlike%20forks%2C%20which%20suffer%20damage%20(repeated%20cycles%20introduce%20work%0Ahardening%20and%20eventual%20fracture)%2C%20many%20hysteretic%20systems%20will%20return%0Ato%20precisely%20the%20same%20state%20after%20being%20cycled.%20%20Magnetic%20tapes%0Acan%20be%20re-recorded%2C%20shape%20memory%20alloys%20can%20be%20cycled%2C%20vortex%20clusters%20can%0Aenter%20and%20leave%20superconductors%2C%20leaving%20the%20system%20in%20largely%20the%0Asame%20state%20it%20began%20in.%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cimg%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cstrong%3EHysteresis%20Loop%20Showing%20Return--Point%20Memory.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%0A%3Cem%3ENote%20that%20the%20system%20returns%20to%20the%20original%20curve%20at%20exactly%20the%20same%0Astate%20B%20that%20it%20left%2C%20that%20the%20returning%20curve%20has%20an%20apparent%20slope%0Adiscontinuity%20at%20B%2C%20and%20that%20both%20effects%20also%20happen%20for%20the%20internal%0Asubloop.%20%20Thus%20a%20state%20can%20have%20a%20whole%20hierarchy%20of%20parent%20states%0A(mothers%20at%20increasing%20fields%20and%20fathers%20at%20decreasing%20fields)%2C%20which%0Aare%20seen%20as%20kinks%20in%20the%20corresponding%20branch%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3EH(M)%3C%2Fem%3E%20curve.%3C%2Fem%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%0AThis%20return--point%20memory%20effect%20is%20also%20known%20as%20%60%60wiping%20out''%2C%20since%0Athe%20memory%20of%20the%20excursion%20is%20wiped%20from%20the%20behavior%20of%20the%20material%0Aas%20soon%20as%20the%20field%20is%20raised%20past%20the%20previous%20extreme%20value.%20%20Subloops%0Aclosing%20may%20not%20seem%20such%20a%20big%20deal%2C%20but%20some%20experimental%0Aacoustic%20emission%20data%20shown%20to%20me%20in%20Barcelona%20(taken%20originally%0Ain%20Mallorca)%2C%20showed%20that%20every%20crackle%20and%20pop%20reproduces%20under%0Acycling!%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fhysteresis%2FRPM_Expt.gif%22%3E%0A%3Cimg%3E%0A%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cstrong%3EReturn%20Point%20Memory%3A%20Experiment.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%20%3Cem%3EAcoustic%20emission%20%0Afrom%20a%20Cu-Zn-Al%20alloy%2C%20measured%20during%20thermal%20cycling%20through%20the%20martensitic%0Atransformation%20(traveling%20repeatedly%20around%20the%20hysteresis%20loop).%20%20A%0Atiny%20portion%20of%20the%20two%20hysteresis%20loops%20is%20shown.%20%20Notice%0Athe%20sharp%20spikes%20from%20the%20various%20pulses%20(avalanches)%3B%20notice%20the%20wide%0Aspectrum%20of%20avalanche%20sizes.%20%20Notice%20the%20excellent%20reproduction%20of%20even%0Athe%20fine%20structure%20when%20the%20loop%20is%20repeated.%3C%2Fem%3E%20%20%0AFrom%20Amengual%20%3Cem%3Eet%20al.%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%0A%3Cem%3EThermochimica%20Acta%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cstrong%3E116%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20195%20(1987).%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%0ASivan%20Kartha%20and%20I%20started%20modeling%20this%20system%2C%20and%20came%20up%20with%0Aa%20rather%20simple%20explanation%20of%20this%20unusual%20effect%20(it%20follows%20from%0Apartial%20ordering%2C%20no%20passing%2C%20and%20adiabaticity%20(Ref.%2066)).%20%20We%20then%20addressed%0Athe%20question%20of%20why%20the%20popping%2C%20crackling%20sounds%20come%20in%20such%20a%20spectrum%0Aof%20sizes...%0A%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fhysteresis%2Fhysteresis.html%22%3E%0AMore%20Information%20about%20Hysteresis%20and%20Avalanches%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%0A%3Cul%20compact%3D%22%22%3E%0A%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fhysteresis%2Fauthors.html%22%3E%0AAuthors%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fhysteresis%2Fhysteresis.html%22%3E%0AHysteresis%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fhysteresis%2FWhatIsHysteresis.html%22%3E%0AWhat%20is%20Hysteresis%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fhysteresis%2Fnoise.html%22%3E%0ANoise%20in%20Hysteresis%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fhysteresis%2FReturnPointMemory.html%22%3E%0AReturn%20Point%20Memory%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fhysteresis%2FHysteresisCriticalPoint.html%22%3E%0AThe%20Critical%20Point%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fhysteresis%2FEpsilonExpansion.html%22%3E%0AThe%20Epsilon%20Expansion%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%0A%0A%3Chr%3E%0A%0A%3Ch2%3ELinks%20Back%3C%2Fh2%3E%0A%3Cdl%20compact%3D%22%22%3E%0A%3Cdt%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fresearch94%2Fresearch94.html%22%3E%0ASethna's%20Research%2090-94%3C%2Fa%3E%0A%3C%2Fdt%3E%3Cdt%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lassp.cornell.edu%2FLASSP_Science.html%22%3E%0A%3Cimg%3E%0AEntertaining%20Science%3C%2Fa%3E%20done%20at%3C%2Fdt%3E%0A%3Cdt%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lassp.cornell.edu%2F%22%3E%0A%3Cimg%3E%20LASSP.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdt%3E%0A%3C%2Fdl%3E%0A%0A%3Chr%3E%0ALast%20modified%3A%20December%2012%2C%201994%3Cp%3E%0A%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fsethna.lassp.cornell.edu%2Fsethna.htm